    }
  ],
  "text": "The error 'mvcc: required revision has been compacted' originates in the authoritative etcd repository (sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd), not from Kubernetes vendored copies. The error is defined as the ErrCompacted variable in server/mvcc/kvstore.go (line 39), where it is declared as: ErrCompacted = errors.New(\"mvcc: required revision has been compacted\"). This error is returned by the core function rangeKeys in server/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go (lines 128-137) when a client requests a revision that has been garbage-collected by compaction. Specifically, rangeKeys checks if the requested revision (rev) is less than the compactMainRev (the main revision cutoff for compaction); if so, it returns the ErrCompacted error. The Kubernetes repository at version 1.32.0 contains vendored copies of this etcd code under vendor/go.etcd.io/etcd/server/v3/mvcc/kvstore.go and vendor/go.etcd.io/etcd/server/v3/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go, but these are merely mirrors of the authoritative source and should NOT be cited for bug reports. The original error definition and the function that propagates it must be traced to the upstream etcd-io/etcd repository to file bugs against the correct component."
}

